Amplitude is a comprehensive digital analytics platform that provides organizations with tools for product analytics, experimentation, data management, and user engagement. The platform enables teams to understand user behavior, optimize product experiences, and drive growth through data-driven insights.

## Core Product Suite

Amplitude consists of four primary products that work together to provide end-to-end analytics and optimization capabilities:

**Amplitude Analytics** serves as the foundational product analytics platform, offering multiple chart types and analysis methods including Event Segmentation charts for understanding user behavior patterns, Funnel Analysis for diagnosing conversion issues, Retention Analysis for measuring product adoption, Stickiness Analysis for identifying power users, Journey Analysis for discovering user paths, Data Tables for multi-dimensional analysis, and User Sessions analysis for measuring engagement duration.

**Amplitude Experiment** provides A/B testing and feature experimentation capabilities, including feature flag management, targeted rollouts, and Web Experimentation for optimizing conversion rates in web experiences and single-page applications.

**Amplitude Data** focuses on data governance and management, offering tools for data taxonomy design, warehouse-native functionality that allows direct querying of data warehouses, and integration capabilities with platforms like Google Ads and HubSpot.

**Amplitude Engage** delivers user engagement tools including Guides and Surveys for in-product messaging, Session Replay for contextualizing user experiences, and Autocapture with visual labeling for tracking website interactions without manual instrumentation.

## Key Features and Analysis Capabilities

The platform provides specialized analysis tools for different use cases. For conversion optimization, Funnel and Path analyses help teams understand user movement through products and identify optimization opportunities. Retention and Stickiness analyses focus on measuring product adoption and identifying highly engaged user segments. The Event Segmentation chart serves as a foundational tool for understanding what drives user behavior across different segments.

Advanced features include Session Replay for qualitative insights into user experiences, Data Tables for analyzing multiple metrics simultaneously, and Journeys for discovering and confirming user paths within products. The platform also supports Autocapture functionality that automatically tracks website clicks and provides visual labeling tools for defining events without manual instrumentation.

## Integration and Data Management

Amplitude supports extensive integration capabilities, including native connections with Google Ads for marketing performance analysis, HubSpot integration for personalizing customer journeys and improving lead scoring, and warehouse-native functionality that enables direct querying of existing data warehouses while maintaining Amplitude's analytics capabilities.

The platform emphasizes proper data taxonomy design through dedicated frameworks and best practices, ensuring organizations can maintain clean, governable data structures that provide continued business value.

## Collaboration and Administration

Amplitude includes robust collaboration features through Spaces, which allow teams to collect and share analytics assets with teammates. The platform provides comprehensive admin tools for setting up and administering Amplitude instances, including user tracking methodologies and governance frameworks.

## Learning and Certification

The Amplitude Academy offers structured learning paths and courses covering all aspects of the platform, from basic analytics concepts to advanced features like warehouse-native implementations and experimentation workflows. The academy provides both video courses and hands-on learning paths, with some courses offering certification badges upon completion.

The platform serves multiple user personas including product managers, growth marketers, data analysts, and administrators, with specialized learning paths and features tailored to each role's specific needs and use cases.